        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} to be 4 hours before departure at the airport.  Google Maps said I need about an hour and a half from the hotel to the airport by taxi. My flight should go at 12:40 p.m., so I ordered the taxi at 7:45 a.m. Of course, this arrived as usual with a few minutes late. But that's due to the many traffic here. Since, thanks to the app, I could see where the vehicle was, it was not all bad. </p>
        <p> After about half an hour of driving, we were already at the airport. Here at the national airport, the processes run a little differently, you first have to be through a security check, after that, after that the check-in switch. Of course, these were almost empty. So it only took 5 minutes for my luggage to be checked in and I had my ticket. I then asked the next security check how long I would need about the gate. The lady looked at me a little in astonishment and said 1 minute. I just thought oh dear, it's just 8:30 a.m. and I don't have to be at the gate until 12:00 p.m. So much to you take 4 hours to get through all security controls and be on the plane in good time. Well, nothing helps. Then I just sat on the next free chair, unpacked my laptop and made on this website. </p>
