    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> The flight later was very relaxed. We even flew past the Mayon volcano, who started spitting Lava a little over a month ago. However, it was not a smoke or a sign of an outbreak to be seen. During the flight, I was traditionally served for the first time Filipino food. There were chicken adobo. This is plucked chicken chest, fried with spices and served on a rice bed. When I accepted the food I thought "Oh dear but there is a lot of garlic in it". After I had the food, which was very tasty by the way, I had the feeling that I urgently needed a toothbrush and mouthwash. When I got out of the plane I already had the feeling "Damn, you stink tremendously for garlic. Poor taxi driver." </p>
        <p> Everything worked well with the accommodation. Have a small but fine apartment on the 19th floor of a high -rise building all for me alone. The view is good and on the 17th floor there is a pool with a great view of the city. I also used it in the evening. Despite that it is always warm here, the pool was pretty fresh. In the evening I also looked at a coworking office. This is almost an office where you can rent a daily desk. The A Space Cebu is very nice and practical and the WLAN speed is nice. Should be enough for the meetings on Wednesday. </p>
        <p> Tomorrow I have completely free again. I will browse a little here and look at the surroundings. </p>
